  "text": "The present work investigated morphological characteristics in the parietal lobes of 60 hemispheres. Thanks to existing methods exploiting the knowledge incorporated in manual delineations for automatically anatomically segmenting large numbers of brain images [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , it is possible to use the present atlases for the study of new control and disease cohorts. Future studies could hence also explore the correspondence between the current anatomical delineations and fMRI distributions of activity.",
